            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": "Discussion",
            "text": "In our literature review, we found that, in more than 85% of these cases, mucormycosis infection occurred after COVID-19 treatment with glucocorticoids. But, only in our case and three other cases, patients had association of COVID-19 and mucormycosis in the absence of taking any treatment, including glucocorticoids, for COVID-19 (Table 1) [9] [10] [11] . In the absence of receiving any treatment for COVID-19, occurrence of mucormycosis may be due to immune dysregulation caused by SARS-CoV-2 virus or immunodeficiency related to DM that was aggravated by COVID-19 [5] ."
        },
